Method Detail

hashCode

public static int hashCode(Throwable throwable,
                           IncludeStackTrace includeStackTrace)
Calculates the hash code of any Throwable. The stack trace may be optionally included which may give surprising results. (It is harder than most realise to create two exceptions with exact same stack trace.)

Parameters:
throwable - any Throwable reference, including null
includeStackTrace - if IncludeStackTrace.YES, stack trace is included in the calculation.
Returns:
if input is null, then 0 (zero), else the hash code, which may or may not include the stack trace
Throws:
NullPointerException - if includeStackTrace is null

equals

public static boolean equals(Throwable throwable1,
                             Throwable throwable2,
                             IncludeStackTrace includeStackTrace)
Compare two Throwable references for equality. Inputs of null (none, one, or both) are handled correctly. The stack trace may be optionally included which may give surprising results. (It is harder than most realise to create two exceptions with exact same stack trace.)

Parameters:
throwable1 - first Throwable for comparison
throwable2 - second Throwable for comparison
includeStackTrace - if IncludeStackTrace.YES, stack trace is included in the calculation.
Returns:
  • true if both Throwables are null
  • true if both Throwables are not null and equals by attribute (message, cause, etc.)
  • false for all other cases
Throws:
NullPointerException - if includeStackTrace is null

toString

@NotFullyTested
public static String toString(Throwable throwable)
Creates a descriptive string useful for debugging from a Throwable reference. Causes are fully recursed via Throwable.getCause().

Parameters:
throwable - non-null Throwable reference
Returns:
string to describe the Throwable reference
Throws:
NullPointerException - if throwable is null
